\description{
An offcanvas is a panel that slides in from an edge of the viewport, built on
\href{https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/components/offcanvas/}{Bootstrap 5's offcanvas component}. It can be
used in three ways:
\enumerate{
\item \strong{With a trigger in the UI.} Pass a \code{trigger} element (e.g. a button);
clicking it reveals the panel.
\item \strong{Controlled from the server.} Give the panel an \code{id}, place it in the UI,
then reveal or hide it with \code{\link[=show_offcanvas]{show_offcanvas()}}, \code{\link[=hide_offcanvas]{hide_offcanvas()}}, or
\code{\link[=toggle_offcanvas]{toggle_offcanvas()}}.
\item \strong{Defined and revealed entirely from the server.} Build the panel in the
server function and pass it to \code{\link[=show_offcanvas]{show_offcanvas()}}.
}
